 The Asset & Resource Management Holding Company Limited (ARM) said it founded the youth talent award to promote innovation and entrepreneurship among undergraduates. In a statement, it added that it was also to promote life-long learning by aiding young  graduates and undergraduates bring their ideas to life. The firm said, in collaboration with TechnoVision Communications Limited (TechnoVision), it has opened applications for the Deji Alli ARM Young Talent Award (DAAYTA)   2020 programme. It said the programme was inaugurated by ARM in 2015 in honour its founding CEO Mr. Deji Alli to enable the youths to live their dreams. The maiden edition of the  programme was held in 2016 and resulted in the selection of a First Class graduate of Computer Science from the University of Lagos as the winner. 